WEBVTT

00:06.390 --> 00:08.780
I love everything about you...

00:09.290 --> 00:13.040
from your beautiful eyes, 
to your too-short bangs.

00:23.590 --> 00:28.490
<i>I didn't understand people 
who rewatched movies.</i>

00:28.490 --> 00:31.790
<i>What's fun about watching a movie 
when you know what happens next?</i>

00:33.170 --> 00:36.380
<i>Going through streaming platforms
because I had nothing better to do,</i>

00:36.380 --> 00:39.020
<i>I found a movie I'd seen 
seven years earlier.</i>

00:40.730 --> 00:45.570
<i>The protagonist repeatedly time travels 
so he can end up with the girl he loves.</i>

00:45.860 --> 00:48.290
<i>It was a popular Hollywood 
film at the time.</i>

00:49.530 --> 00:53.990
<b>Hazy Low-Malt Beer</b>

00:50.070 --> 00:53.500
<i>I learned something
from rewatching that movie.</i>

00:54.430 --> 00:59.380
<i>Knowing what happens next is 
what grants you the perspective</i>

00:59.380 --> 01:01.420
<i>to know what you 
should've done instead.</i>

01:08.010 --> 01:09.800
<i>That made me realize something.</i>

01:10.510 --> 01:15.760
<i>That I'd been having those kinds 
of thoughts for a long time.</i>

01:16.750 --> 01:18.950
<i>Looking back on my life 
with a broader perspective,</i>

01:18.950 --> 01:25.400
<i>that moment from my first year of high 
school was undoubtedly a turning point.</i>

01:27.100 --> 01:31.100
Sorry, Natsuki. I can't keep 
covering for you.

01:31.100 --> 01:34.720
And more to the point, you piss me off.

01:44.100 --> 01:48.210
<i>I tried to become an outgoing person 
in high school and failed spectacularly.</i>

01:49.940 --> 01:58.360
<i>The best way to describe my three high 
school years would be "colorless and gray."</i>

02:01.830 --> 02:06.360
<i>I learned from my mistakes 
and avoided disaster in college.</i>

02:06.360 --> 02:09.410
<i>I successfully completed 
the credits I needed to graduate</i>

02:09.410 --> 02:13.590
<i>and secured a stable future
at an infrastructure company.</i>

02:14.850 --> 02:19.640
<i>I'll have an ordinary graduation, get an 
ordinary job, and live an ordinary life.</i>

02:20.110 --> 02:23.960
<i>I'm sure I'll be happy 
with an ordinary life.</i>

02:24.380 --> 02:27.920
<i>But my teenage regrets will never go away.</i>

02:28.720 --> 02:32.290
<i>If what I wanted was 
rainbow-colored teenage years,</i>

02:32.290 --> 02:34.520
<i>then that will never be mine.</i>

02:35.150 --> 02:36.340
H-Hoshimiya-san.

02:36.720 --> 02:38.040
I've always had a crush on you.

02:38.040 --> 02:39.560
Please go out with me.

02:41.220 --> 02:43.120
I'm sorry.

02:47.860 --> 02:48.100
Ho

02:48.100 --> 02:48.350
Hoshi

02:48.350 --> 02:48.600
Hoshimi

02:48.600 --> 02:49.480
Hoshimiya

02:49.480 --> 02:49.730
Hoshimiya Hi

02:49.730 --> 02:49.980
Hoshimiya Hika

02:49.980 --> 02:50.850
Hoshimiya Hikari

02:50.850 --> 02:51.020
Hoshimiya Hik

02:51.020 --> 02:51.190
Hoshimiya

02:51.190 --> 02:51.350
Hoshi

02:51.350 --> 02:51.570
Ho

02:51.570 --> 02:54.110
<i>Everyone experiences 
that kind of sentimentality.</i>

02:54.110 --> 02:59.030
<i>Everyone regrets their teens 
not going the way they wanted.</i>

02:59.520 --> 03:01.320
<i>Yeah, I know.</i>

03:01.860 --> 03:08.000
<i>That's why all I'm doing
is offering a little prayer.</i>

03:08.580 --> 03:15.050
<i>If possible, I'd love 
to redo my teenage years.</i>

03:23.930 --> 03:25.520
Ow...

03:36.610 --> 03:37.750
What?!

03:39.590 --> 03:44.540
<b>Episode 1</b>

03:39.590 --> 03:44.540
<b>The Gray Boy's Plan For a Colorful Adolescence</b>

03:40.480 --> 03:42.450
What? Is this me?

03:44.260 --> 03:47.040
I heard a loud noise. Are you okay?

03:51.870 --> 03:52.840
Is that cosplay?

03:53.150 --> 03:55.920
Huh? What're you on about?

03:56.940 --> 03:59.440
<i>Namika is starting her 
second year of college this year.</i>

03:59.440 --> 04:02.890
<i>She's way too old to accidentally 
put on her middle school uniform.</i>

04:04.000 --> 04:09.790
<i>If possible, I'd love 
to redo my teenage years.</i>

04:11.200 --> 04:12.020
<i>Could it be?</i>

04:12.690 --> 04:16.190
N-Namika, what year is it?

04:16.190 --> 04:20.110
What? It's 2014. What about it?

04:23.750 --> 04:26.000
What's wrong with you?

04:26.330 --> 04:29.640
Nothing. I just feel a little unwell.

04:30.630 --> 04:33.960
Well, it's a good thing 
you already graduated.

04:33.960 --> 04:35.800
Get some rest.

04:46.430 --> 04:48.140
March 10th (Mon)

04:48.140 --> 04:50.280
<i>I've returned to my past.</i>

04:50.710 --> 04:54.900
<i>Have I time traveled 
like in an anime or manga?</i>

04:54.900 --> 04:58.110
<i>I must be consuming 
too much of that stuff.</i>

05:02.320 --> 05:04.080
<i>This has to be a dream.</i>

05:04.080 --> 05:08.120
<i>Time travel doesn't happen in real life.</i>

05:14.230 --> 05:15.790
Natsuki, are you in here?

05:17.210 --> 05:18.800
Congratulations on graduating.

05:20.740 --> 05:21.760
Mom?

05:22.220 --> 05:24.480
Sorry I couldn't attend the ceremony.

05:24.480 --> 05:27.220
Of all the times to have work...

05:27.520 --> 05:30.930
Oh? You look kind of pale.

05:31.340 --> 05:33.300
Are you feeling sick?

05:33.300 --> 05:36.400
A little. Can I sleep until dinner?

05:36.690 --> 05:39.430
Sure. Did you take your temperature?

05:39.430 --> 05:41.050
Do we have any fever patches?

05:41.050 --> 05:43.240
Don't worry about it.

05:46.720 --> 05:49.570
<i>I woke up, but I'm still dreaming.</i>

05:49.990 --> 05:53.210
<i>No, this isn't a dream. It's reality.</i>

05:54.080 --> 05:56.830
<i>There's no point in wondering 
how this happened.</i>

05:56.830 --> 05:58.570
<i>I'd never figure it out.</i>

05:59.340 --> 06:01.590
<i>So I should focus on the bottom line.</i>

06:01.590 --> 06:04.500
<i>Starting today, I'm redoing my life.</i>

06:05.540 --> 06:09.160
<i>I can redo my disastrous 
high school experience.</i>

06:10.230 --> 06:12.830
<i>This time, I'll live 
my teens to the fullest.</i>

06:12.830 --> 06:16.740
<i>I'll repaint my gray adolescence 
with a rainbow of color.</i>

06:19.610 --> 06:22.900
<i>I had plenty of ideas for what I could do.</i>

06:23.480 --> 06:27.000
<i>After all, I've thought about 
what I should've done</i>

06:27.000 --> 06:30.640
<i>thousands of times since
my first year of high school.</i>

06:33.660 --> 06:36.800
<i>I have roughly one month until 
my high school entrance ceremony.</i>

06:36.800 --> 06:40.130
<i>I'll use that time to improve myself.</i>

06:43.720 --> 06:44.850
I'm gonna die...

06:45.310 --> 06:50.440
<i>Before, I would've made some kind 
of excuse and given up here.</i>

06:55.600 --> 06:57.620
<i>But I'm different now.</i>

06:58.460 --> 07:03.200
<i>I don't want to go through those 
miserable, gray teenage years again.</i>

07:03.570 --> 07:07.560
<i>When I think of it that way, 
I can endure anything.</i>

07:23.200 --> 07:26.590
<i>And so, a month flew by 
in the blink of an eye.</i>

07:31.310 --> 07:34.020
You... <i>are</i> my brother, right?

07:34.810 --> 07:36.010
Of course I am.

07:36.010 --> 07:37.230
What do you think?

07:37.640 --> 07:39.480
Not bad.

07:39.890 --> 07:41.160
Not that I care.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.000
<i>The time to prepare is over.</i>

07:47.360 --> 07:49.260
<i>The entrance ceremony is next.</i>

07:49.260 --> 07:50.700
<i>My real test starts today.</i>

07:59.950 --> 08:01.160
Natsuki?

08:01.940 --> 08:04.800
Miori? I haven't seen you 
since graduation.

08:05.660 --> 08:07.360
<i>Motomiya Miori.</i>

08:07.360 --> 08:11.150
<i>We've attended the same 
school since kindergarten.</i>

08:11.150 --> 08:14.260
<i>She's what you'd call a childhood friend.</i>

08:14.720 --> 08:18.420
You seem... really different.

08:18.950 --> 08:22.940
I had some free time over spring break, 
so I did some strength training.

08:22.940 --> 08:24.570
I'm on a jog right now.

08:26.610 --> 08:28.700
It's like you're a whole new person.

08:28.700 --> 08:30.240
This that "high school debut" thing?

08:32.270 --> 08:34.200
So? Is that a problem?

08:34.530 --> 08:37.700
Not at all. In fact, it's a good thing.

08:38.710 --> 08:41.660
If anything, you were
kinda lame until now.

08:42.120 --> 08:43.800
And overweight, too.

08:44.670 --> 08:48.340
But you've always had potential. 
You just needed to try.

08:49.720 --> 08:52.360
Well, you've changed a lot, too.

08:52.360 --> 08:54.230
What? I have?

08:54.230 --> 08:58.300
I guess we were always in different 
classes during middle school.

08:58.300 --> 09:01.820
And since you didn't have friends, 
we never had a reason to talk.

09:01.820 --> 09:03.360
Oh, shut up.

09:05.400 --> 09:11.000
Unfortunately, the cool Miori-chan 
you used to like is gone now.

09:11.000 --> 09:12.000
Sorry.

09:12.360 --> 09:15.330
Cool? You were just a snot-nosed tomboy.

09:15.330 --> 09:16.720
Who are you calling a tomboy?!

09:16.720 --> 09:19.120
I was just a little tough!

09:19.880 --> 09:22.680
Sorry, Ku-chan. See you later.

09:23.920 --> 09:25.090
Oh, Natsuki.

09:25.420 --> 09:27.060
Where are you going for high school?

09:27.060 --> 09:29.300
Ryomei. Ryomei High School.

09:29.600 --> 09:32.090
What? We're going to the same school?

09:33.580 --> 09:37.860
By the way, I knew we were the only ones 
attending from our middle school.

09:37.860 --> 09:40.390
Seriously? You should've told me sooner!

09:40.730 --> 09:45.350
When? We never had a reason to talk.

09:56.540 --> 09:59.320
<i>I-I feel like everyone's looking at me.</i>

10:00.070 --> 10:03.170
<i>Do I still look like a creep 
even after I lost weight?!</i>

10:25.310 --> 10:28.060
<i>Hoshimiya Hikari...</i>

10:35.910 --> 10:38.180
Hikari? Is something wrong?

10:38.180 --> 10:40.370
No, it's nothing.

10:41.940 --> 10:43.650
<i>Rainbow-colored teenage years...</i>

10:44.140 --> 10:47.830
<i>I thought it was just a vague goal I had,</i>

10:48.230 --> 10:52.420
<i>but this gave me clear direction.</i>

10:53.210 --> 10:55.590
<i>I wanted Hoshimiya to like me.</i>

10:55.590 --> 10:58.390
<i>This time, I'd go out with her.</i>

11:11.610 --> 11:13.310
Class 1-2

11:13.310 --> 11:14.070
<b>Haibara Natsuki</b>

11:14.340 --> 11:16.250
<i>Class 1-2.</i>

11:16.250 --> 11:18.490
<i>That's the same as before, which means...</i>

11:17.650 --> 11:18.870
<b>Hoshimiya Hikari</b>

11:19.220 --> 11:22.110
<i>I knew it. Hoshimiya's in the same class.</i>

11:22.110 --> 11:26.330
Hey, look, look. We're in 
the same class, Rei and Tatsu.

11:26.330 --> 11:30.040
I know. You don't have to shout.

11:30.540 --> 11:34.650
Uta's just excited 
about starting high school.

11:34.650 --> 11:36.890
I know you're happy, too, Tatsu.

11:36.890 --> 11:38.730
Don't try to act cool about it.

11:38.730 --> 11:43.270
What? Why would I be happy 
about being in the same class as you?

11:43.270 --> 11:45.820
You're such a tsundere, Tatsuya.

11:47.440 --> 11:50.440
Oh, sorry. They're noisy, aren't they?

11:50.440 --> 11:55.440
Not at all. I was just thinking 
you seem like good friends.

11:55.930 --> 11:59.220
The three of us attended 
the same middle school.

11:59.220 --> 12:00.910
Are you in class 1-2, too?

12:01.220 --> 12:04.620
Yeah. I'm Haibara Natsuki. 
Nice to meet you.

12:05.050 --> 12:06.710
I'm Shiratori Reita.

12:09.370 --> 12:10.750
I'm Nagiura Tatsuya.

12:12.770 --> 12:16.670
And more to the point, you piss me off.

12:19.920 --> 12:22.470
You know, you're pretty fit.

12:23.010 --> 12:24.930
What club were you in?

12:24.930 --> 12:28.600
No club. I just went straight home after
classes during middle school.

12:28.900 --> 12:33.320
Seriously? You seem oddly built for that.

12:33.650 --> 12:35.530
I do strength training for fun.

12:35.530 --> 12:37.310
I'm glad to hear you say—

12:37.310 --> 12:38.010
Wha?!

12:38.010 --> 12:40.950
Oh, wow! You've got abs!

12:44.070 --> 12:47.380
I'm Sakura Uta. Call me Uta.

12:53.540 --> 12:56.000
I spy someone really cute!

12:56.340 --> 12:58.780
Huh? Who, me?

12:58.780 --> 13:02.800
Yeah. You're even super cute up close.

13:03.090 --> 13:04.800
Th-Thank you.

13:04.800 --> 13:06.470
I'm gonna make you mine!

13:06.470 --> 13:08.520
Wha? But...

13:09.600 --> 13:13.440
That's enough, Uta. You're scaring her.

13:13.710 --> 13:16.200
But she's so cute!

13:16.710 --> 13:17.940
Isn't she?

13:18.190 --> 13:21.660
Hikari was the most popular
girl at our middle school.

13:21.660 --> 13:24.490
Don't, Yuino-chan.

13:24.900 --> 13:26.950
<i>Outgoing people have 
crazy social skills...</i>

13:27.440 --> 13:31.410
<i>Wait, is this already my chance 
to get close to Hoshimiya?</i>

13:27.700 --> 13:29.290
It's true, though.

13:29.290 --> 13:30.900
No, it's not.

13:31.740 --> 13:34.380
You attended the same middle school?

13:34.710 --> 13:37.030
Yeah, Kasai Middle School.

13:37.030 --> 13:38.090
What about you guys?

13:38.490 --> 13:40.720
We went to Oshima Middle School.

13:41.420 --> 13:43.690
Well, except for Natsu.

13:44.650 --> 13:48.500
Oh, right. I went to Mizumi Middle School.

13:48.500 --> 13:50.350
It's a little far from here.

13:50.900 --> 13:54.570
Isn't that in Takasaki?

13:54.570 --> 13:59.320
Not exactly, but more or less.

13:59.950 --> 14:01.480
<i>C-Crap.</i>

14:01.860 --> 14:08.760
<i>I bet they're wondering what an awkward 
loser is doing with the popular crowd.</i>

14:09.450 --> 14:12.920
I'm Nanase Yuino, Hikari's best friend.

14:13.420 --> 14:16.810
That's right. We're best friends.

14:16.810 --> 14:18.790
I'm Hoshimiya Hikari.

14:18.790 --> 14:23.480
She's the most beautiful girl in school 
and likes to read and watch movies.

14:23.480 --> 14:25.640
She was in the literature club 
in middle school.

14:25.640 --> 14:26.550
Yeah.

14:27.010 --> 14:29.970
Wait, no! I'm not beautiful!

14:34.540 --> 14:37.060
I don't think you can claim 
you're not beautiful.

14:40.080 --> 14:40.860
<i>Crap.</i>

14:42.800 --> 14:44.570
Th-Thanks.

14:44.570 --> 14:47.530
No, I'm sorry. It just slipped out.

14:47.850 --> 14:51.020
Oh? You don't often blush, Hikari.

14:51.020 --> 14:53.050
I thought you were used 
to being called beautiful.

14:53.050 --> 14:56.040
Come on, Yuino-chan. 
Stop pressing my buttons.

14:56.040 --> 14:57.220
Okay, okay.

14:57.220 --> 14:58.500
Sheesh.

14:58.880 --> 15:05.600
<i>And that's how my plan for a colorful 
adolescence started off with a bang.</i>

15:07.070 --> 15:11.640
<i>Additionally, during standard 
homeroom introductions...</i>

15:13.630 --> 15:16.180
My name is Haibara Natsuki.

15:16.180 --> 15:19.760
I like reading and watching movies.

15:19.760 --> 15:24.900
I'm hoping to join the basketball team, 
and my dream is to make a hundred friends.

15:28.470 --> 15:31.120
I hope we can all be friends.

15:31.120 --> 15:32.320
Nice to meet you!

15:32.950 --> 15:37.890
<i>No, stop! Don't replay 
your embarrassing past!</i>

15:41.370 --> 15:43.010
Hey, Natsu.

15:43.740 --> 15:45.840
You'll check out clubs with us, right?

15:47.250 --> 15:48.360
Of course.

15:48.800 --> 15:50.890
<b>Library</b>

15:52.460 --> 15:55.600
Hello. Could we sit in on your club?

15:56.290 --> 15:58.560
Y-Yes, of course.

15:59.070 --> 16:01.800
You're the literature club, right?

16:01.800 --> 16:03.060
Th-That's us.

16:03.060 --> 16:04.940
Uh... Umm...

16:04.940 --> 16:07.530
You're new students, right?

16:07.830 --> 16:10.770
Yes, we're new.

16:10.770 --> 16:12.490
<i>I've heard about this.</i>

16:12.490 --> 16:15.970
<i>They say truly outgoing people even 
know how to handle awkward people.</i>

16:15.970 --> 16:18.290
<i>Looks like there's some truth to it.</i>

16:21.770 --> 16:23.250
Hey!

16:24.820 --> 16:27.060
I knew it was you, Shiratori.

16:27.060 --> 16:28.660
You came to this school?

16:28.660 --> 16:30.730
Oshima's captain, huh?

16:30.730 --> 16:32.700
You're joining the soccer team, right?

16:32.700 --> 16:35.350
It's been a while.
Do you recognize me?

16:35.820 --> 16:38.300
You're Fuji Middle School's three idiots.

16:38.300 --> 16:39.560
It's good to see you again.

16:39.560 --> 16:41.440
Who are you calling idiots?!

16:46.550 --> 16:47.920
You're like a little kid.

16:48.600 --> 16:51.250
Are you talking about my height?

16:51.250 --> 16:53.120
Not exactly.

16:53.120 --> 16:55.430
Was it my chest, then?

16:55.430 --> 16:59.220
Just so you know, 
I'm just starting to grow.

16:59.220 --> 17:02.960
If anything, I've got 
nothing <i>but</i> room for growth.

17:03.390 --> 17:09.090
Yes, my chest has unlimited potential.

17:09.490 --> 17:13.300
Why are you depressing yourself 
with your own explanation?

17:13.300 --> 17:14.640
Hey, Nagiura!

17:15.480 --> 17:18.270
If you've got time to screw around,
you've got time to practice.

17:18.270 --> 17:21.020
Can't I just watch today?

17:21.470 --> 17:24.480
Prepare to be run ragged!

17:22.670 --> 17:24.480
You're strangling me!

17:25.750 --> 17:26.940
Hey.

17:27.500 --> 17:28.760
Miori.

17:32.470 --> 17:35.820
<i>Don't do it. Please just 
keep your mouth shut.</i>

17:36.780 --> 17:39.700
You seem to be doing pretty well, Natsuki.

17:39.700 --> 17:42.580
Please just shut up.

17:42.580 --> 17:43.790
You know each other?

17:44.300 --> 17:46.000
We went to the same middle school.

17:46.000 --> 17:48.550
Oh? You seem close.

17:48.550 --> 17:52.590
Oh, not at all. Not in the slightest.

17:48.550 --> 17:50.060
Not really.

17:52.960 --> 17:55.180
Anyway, you're really handsome.

17:55.180 --> 17:58.390
Thanks. I'm Shiratori Reita.

17:58.660 --> 18:01.600
I'm Miori. Can I call you Reita-kun?

18:01.900 --> 18:04.850
Sure. Can I call you Miori-chan?

18:04.850 --> 18:07.020
Or would you prefer something else?

18:07.020 --> 18:09.490
That's fine, but you could 
drop the honorifics entirely.

18:12.890 --> 18:15.460
Your high school debut's going well.

18:15.460 --> 18:17.200
Leave me alone.

18:18.030 --> 18:20.500
That's definitely not happening.

18:22.000 --> 18:25.620
I like Reita-kun. Be my wingman.

18:25.620 --> 18:26.710
What?

18:27.230 --> 18:30.930
I'll help you with something in exchange.

18:32.450 --> 18:36.640
<i>The first week after 
the entrance ceremony flew by.</i>

18:39.060 --> 18:41.460
What's wrong, Uta?

18:41.460 --> 18:43.100
Practice is canceled tomorrow

18:43.100 --> 18:45.940
and the day after because
they're doing work on the gym.

18:45.940 --> 18:50.400
Ugh! I thought I'd get 
to play basketball all weekend!

18:50.710 --> 18:53.610
Then let's go somewhere, Uta-chan.

18:53.610 --> 18:55.070
What? Really?

18:55.070 --> 18:56.440
We should totally go!

18:56.440 --> 18:58.280
Hooray, a date with Hikarin!

18:58.680 --> 19:02.290
Why don't we all go? I'm free, too.

19:02.550 --> 19:04.980
What? No way.

19:04.980 --> 19:07.660
Are you trying to interfere 
with my date with Hikarin?

19:07.660 --> 19:09.410
Now, now, Uta-chan.

19:09.410 --> 19:13.510
It's a good opportunity, 
and it'd be more fun together.

19:13.990 --> 19:16.220
If Hikari's going, I'm going.

19:16.690 --> 19:21.640
My club's still meeting.
But I could go Saturday afternoon.

19:22.510 --> 19:26.140
Huh? Oh, I'm available. 
I'm not in a club.

19:26.490 --> 19:28.420
Then see you tomorrow afternoon.

19:28.420 --> 19:29.610
All right!

19:35.460 --> 19:37.190
Huh? Hoshimiya?

19:38.220 --> 19:39.990
Are you walking home by yourself today?

19:39.990 --> 19:43.450
Yeah. Yuino-chan has something to do.

19:45.160 --> 19:47.960
Then let's walk home together.

19:52.810 --> 19:57.470
Aren't you in the literature club? 
They're not meeting?

19:57.470 --> 20:01.050
I am, but we only meet 
twice a week on weekdays.

20:01.050 --> 20:03.010
Oh, I see.

20:03.950 --> 20:07.020
<i>Hoshimiya's club doesn't meet on Fridays.</i>

20:07.550 --> 20:12.980
<i>Nanase, her usual companion, has 
lessons on Fridays and leaves without her.</i>

20:13.510 --> 20:16.070
<i>I figured that out during the past week.</i>

20:17.360 --> 20:19.860
<i>I'm just inviting her 
to walk home together.</i>

20:20.470 --> 20:22.880
<i>That's totally normal 
for an outgoing person.</i>

20:22.880 --> 20:27.680
<i>But an introvert like me can't do it 
without planning to a creepy degree.</i>

20:28.490 --> 20:30.360
What should we do tomorrow?

20:30.360 --> 20:34.500
Everyone went off to their club meetings 
without making concrete plans.

20:35.030 --> 20:38.350
We can decide online tonight.

20:38.700 --> 20:41.110
But we haven't made a group chat.

20:41.110 --> 20:45.720
Now that you mention it, you're right. 
I assumed there already was one.

20:45.720 --> 20:46.600
Me, too.

20:48.120 --> 20:50.420
Should we make one now?

20:50.420 --> 20:51.770
What should we call it?

20:55.090 --> 20:57.570
The Hoshimiya Fan Club.

20:57.570 --> 21:01.280
Isn't it weird for me 
to make a group called that?

21:01.610 --> 21:02.760
True.

21:06.750 --> 21:09.390
The Natsuki-kun Fan Club it is.

21:09.390 --> 21:11.620
I don't have any fans.

21:16.720 --> 21:19.130
The Natsuki-kun Family, then.

21:19.130 --> 21:20.560
Hey...

21:23.090 --> 21:24.680
<b>Natsuki-kun Family</b>

21:24.980 --> 21:26.540
Did you get my invite?

21:26.540 --> 21:28.360
Yeah, I did.

21:29.470 --> 21:30.890
Nanase joined, too.

21:30.890 --> 21:32.740
Look this way, Natsuki-kun.

21:32.740 --> 21:33.540
Huh?

21:37.170 --> 21:38.690
Got your picture.

21:40.150 --> 21:42.670
Why would you do that?

21:42.670 --> 21:44.990
To set it as the group icon, obviously.

21:45.420 --> 21:47.450
After all, we're the Natsuki-kun Family.

21:48.830 --> 21:51.260
Then look this way, Hoshimiya.

21:55.180 --> 21:57.620
Hey, wait! Natsuki-kun?

21:57.620 --> 21:58.630
Got you back.

